## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### ❌ Don't call store methods directly during render

Store methods return values directly from the valtio proxy state but **do not subscribe to changes**. When called during render, the component won't re-render when the data changes. Always use the corresponding hooks instead.

| Store Method (Non-reactive) | Hook (Reactive) |
|-----------------------------|-----------------|
| `store.rows()` | `useRows(store)` or `useDBRows(store)` |
| `store.list()` | `useRows(store)` |
| `store.dbList()` | `useDBRows(store)` |
| `store.rowIds()` | `useRowIds(store)` |
| `store.currentRow()` | `useCurrentRow(store)` or `useCurrentRowSync(store)` |
| `store.currentRowId()` | `useCurrentRowId(store)` |
| `store.isLoading()` | `useIsStoreLoading(store)` |
| `store.isPosting()` | `useIsStorePosting(store)` |
| `store.isBusy()` | `useIsStoreBusy(store)` |
| `store.isStoreDirty()` | `useIsStoreDirty(store)` |
| `store.selectedRowIds()` | `useSelectedRowIds(store)` |
| `store.selectedRows()` | `useSelectedRows(store)` |
| `store.hasMoreRows()` | `useHasMoreRows(store)` |
| `store.getSize()` | `useStoreSize(store)` |
| `store.getSort()` | `useFullSortState(store)` |
| `store.getOffset()` | `useStoreOffset(store)` |
| `store.error()` | `useStoreError(store)` |

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong - won't re-render when rows change
function MyComponent({ store }: Props) {
  const rows = store.rows();           // Non-reactive!
  const isLoading = store.isLoading(); // Non-reactive!
  return <div>{rows.length} items</div>;
}

// ✅ Correct - subscribes to changes, triggers re-render
function MyComponent({ store }: Props) {
  const rows = useDBRows(store);
  const isLoading = useIsStoreLoading(store);
  return <div>{rows.length} items</div>;
}
```

**Exception**: Store methods ARE safe to call in event handlers, useEffect callbacks, and async functions (outside of render):

```typescript
// ✅ OK in event handlers
const handleClick = () => {
  const currentId = store.currentRowId();
  const isDirty = store.isStoreDirty();
  if (isDirty) {
    // handle dirty state
  }
};

// ✅ OK in useEffect
useEffect(() => {
  if (store.hasMoreRows()) {
    // do something
  }
}, [someOtherDep]);
```

### ❌ Don't initialize store in useEffect for dialogs

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong - causes timing issues
useEffect(() => {
  if (open) store.createNew({ ... });
}, [open]);

// ✅ Correct - initialize before opening
const handleAdd = () => {
  store.createNew({ ... });
  setOpen(true);
};
```

### ❌ Don't call executeQuery or refresh after save

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong - unnecessary, save auto-refreshes
await store.save();
await store.executeQuery();

// ❌ Wrong - also unnecessary
await store.save();
await store.refresh();

// ✅ Correct - just save
await store.save({ feedback: 'Saved successfully' });

// ✅ Only refresh a DIFFERENT store after cascade delete
await rolesStore.save({ feedback: 'Role deleted' });
assignmentsStore.refresh();  // Different store, cascade-deleted by DB
```

### ❌ Don't use useCurrentRow for form fields

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong - causes cursor jumping in inputs
const row = useCurrentRow(store);

// ✅ Correct - sync mode for forms
const row = useCurrentRowSync(store);
```

### ❌ Don't create stores with same key but different configs

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong - second config is ignored (same key)
const store1 = useStore({ datasourceId: 'Users', page: 'users', alias: 'list', limit: 20 });
const store2 = useStore({ datasourceId: 'Users', page: 'users', alias: 'list', limit: 50 });

// ✅ Correct - use different alias for different configs
const listStore = useStore({ datasourceId: 'Users', page: 'users', alias: 'users-list', limit: 20 });
const exportStore = useStore({ datasourceId: 'Users', page: 'users', alias: 'users-export', limit: 1000 });
```

### ❌ Don't forget to save after deleteRow for DB rows

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong - row is only marked for deletion, not persisted
await store.deleteRow(rowId);

// ✅ Correct - save to persist the deletion
await store.deleteRow(rowId);
if (store.isRowFromDB(rowId)) {
  await store.save();
}
```

### ❌ Don't add manual query deduplication guards

The store handles query deduplication internally. If the same query is called again, it's automatically skipped.

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong - unnecessary guards
useEffect(() => {
  if (row?.projectId === projectId) return;  // Redundant
  store.executeQuery({ query: { match: { projectId } } });
}, [projectId, store, row?.projectId]);

// ❌ Also wrong - useRef tracking is unnecessary
const queriedIdRef = useRef<string | null>(null);
useEffect(() => {
  if (queriedIdRef.current === projectId) return;
  queriedIdRef.current = projectId;
  store.executeQuery({ query: { match: { projectId } } });
}, [projectId, store]);

// ✅ Correct - just call executeQuery
useEffect(() => {
  store.executeQuery({ query: { match: { projectId } } });
}, [projectId, store]);
```

### ❌ Don't have multiple useEffects calling executeQuery

Consolidate into a single effect to avoid duplicate queries on mount.

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong - both effects run on mount
useEffect(() => {
  if (customerId) store.setSmartSearchFilters([...]);
  store.executeQuery();
}, [customerId, store]);

useEffect(() => {
  store.executeQuery();  // Duplicate!
}, [includeArchived, store]);

// ✅ Correct - single effect
useEffect(() => {
  if (customerId) store.setSmartSearchFilters([...]);
  store.executeQuery();
}, [customerId, includeArchived, store]);
```

### ❌ Don't use deprecated `data` or `filter` properties

```typescript
// ❌ Deprecated
store.executeQuery({ query: { data: { projectId } } });
store.executeQuery({ query: { filter: [{ status: { is: 'active' } }] } });

// ✅ Correct - use match and filters
store.executeQuery({ query: { match: { projectId } } });
store.executeQuery({ query: { filters: [{ status: { is: 'active' } }] } });
```

